50|$|The PX-8 did {{not have}} any {{internal}} disk drive, and instead allowed either memory to be partitioned into application memory and a <b>RAM</b> <b>disk,</b> or an external 60 KB or 120 KB intelligent <b>RAM</b> <b>disk</b> module to be attached (64K and 128K internally but some used for the processor). The intelligent <b>RAM</b> <b>disk</b> module had its own Z80 processor with a backup battery.|$|E
